<item>
            <title>[LU-4029] DNE (distributed namespace) and legacy filesystems</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4029</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As part of the training class ongoing in HF3-TR4 with Brett Lee . . . the question came up that when DNE is fully supported, how will legacy systems take advantage of this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The crude answer is to temporarily rename all 10PB of disk files, then rename them back.  This should trigger a rebalance of the metadata.  Obviously that&apos;s not a very good solution, so the question is whether a tuning parameter or the like could be added - or perhaps a new tool - that would rebalance files and directories in DNE.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
